  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, tear your<strong> white cup mushrooms</strong> into the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min, stirring occasionally until golden and caramelised</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-lean-pork-and-mushroom-tortiglioni-with-basil/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the mushrooms are cooking, add your <strong>tortiglioni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> tortiglioni</strong> for 7-9 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the<strong> tortiglioni</strong>, reserving a large cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-lean-pork-and-mushroom-tortiglioni-with-basil/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle</p><p>Once the mushrooms are golden, add your <strong>lean pork mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!)</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until browned all over, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-lean-pork-and-mushroom-tortiglioni-with-basil/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[510ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-lean-pork-and-mushroom-tortiglioni-with-basil/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pork is browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the <strong>tomato stock</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until thickened to the consistency of a ragù</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-lean-pork-and-mushroom-tortiglioni-with-basil/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-lean-pork-and-mushroom-tortiglioni-with-basil/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the ragù has thickened, add your <strong>soft cheese </strong>and <strong>drained tortiglioni</strong> to the pan with a splash of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and stir until the sauce coats the pasta and the pork is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>creamy lean pork and mushroom tortiglioni</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash more starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-lean-pork-and-mushroom-tortiglioni-with-basil/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> creamy lean pork and mushroom tortiglioni</strong> topped with the <strong>grated cheese</strong> and <strong>chopped basil</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
